Step 1 — Create a Repository on Bitbucket
Log in to your Bitbucket account.
Click Create → Repository.
Repository name: BitbucketGitOps
Do NOT add README or .gitignore (we will create files manually)
Click Create repository

Step 2 — Clone the repository locally
Open Git Bash:
git clone https://<username>@bitbucket.org/<username>/BitbucketGitOps.git
cd BitbucketGitOps

Task 2: Create a file example.txt, add and commit it, and create a branch feature
Create the file
echo "This is an example file." > example.txt

Add and commit
git add example.txt
git commit -m "Added example.txt"

Create a new branch named feature
git checkout -b feature


Optional: make a small edit

echo "Feature branch update." >> example.txt
git add example.txt
git commit -m "Updated example.txt in feature branch"

Task 3: Push the feature branch, create PR, review & merge
Push the feature branch to Bitbucket
git push -u origin feature

Create Pull Request on Bitbucket
Go to Bitbucket → your repository.
Click Branches.
Find feature.
Click Create pull request.
Source branch: feature
Destination branch: main
Add title: "Merge feature into main"
Click Create pull request

Review and Merge Pull Request
Open the pull request.
Click Diff to review the changes.
Click Merge at the bottom right.
Choose Merge commit (default) and confirm.

